<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Status-bar notification icon. Deliberately a small, flat, single-color vector —
  NOT the adaptive launcher icon (`ic_launcher`, background+foreground layers),
  which the system cannot silhouette correctly for the status bar. Android renders
  this as a solid alpha mask (tinted white/black by the OS theme), so only the
  shape matters, not the fillColor value itself. Reuses the launcher's own
  concentric-ripple motif at a simplified two-ring weight so it's still
  recognisably "Ripple" at 24dp.
-->
